    {
      "id": "CJrGkqDK5lHPaRJ1Jw5fp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 237,
      "y": 244.5,
      "width": 747.6395263671875,
      "height": 1500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bgJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2110098283,
      "version": 1179,
      "versionNonce": 1057382891,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783675938515,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Req:\n\nq. Are we building a system like datadog or metric monitoring for tech giant?\ninternal tool, non multi tenant \n\nq. features?\nDashboard : show metrics and aggregate them by time\nAlerts: in various channels like msg, on call alerts, slack etc\nMetrics:\nOS metrics: CPU, memory, disk usage\nhigh level concepts : RPS, server count, latency, throughput, availability\nbusiness metrics: custom can be defined\n\nq. scale?\n100 m DAU\nservices? 1000 services and 100 nodes for each and 100 metrics per service\n\nq. write frequency?\nrecord data every second\n\nq. do we need to compact the freq? like \n7 days, no compaction\n8 to 30 days, rol up to 1 min\n> 30 days < 1 year : roll up 10 mins\n> 1 year : archieve\n\nq. logs collection?\nno\n\nq. dist tracing?\nno\n\n\nFunctioanl req:\n1. View Dashboard : show metrics and aggregate them by time\n2. Send Alerts: in various channels like msg, on call alerts, slack etc\n3. Collect Metrics:\nOS metrics: CPU, memory, disk usage\nhigh level concepts : RPS, server count, latency, throughput, availability\nbusiness metrics: custom can be defined\n\nNFR:\n- Availability ( all 3 flows : 99.9)\n- Durability 11 9s\n- Scalable\n- Reliable and fault tolerant\n\nBack of teh enevelop calc:\nview dashboard:\n100 m DAU\n100 * 10^6 / 10^5 = 1000 rps\n\n1000 services * 100 nodes for each * 100 metrics per service\n= 10m metrics writes per second\n\nalerts:\nwhen alerts are raised, assume 0.1%\n10k alerts. pers sec\n\nservices? 1000 services and 100 nodes for each and 100 metrics per service",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Req:\n\nq. Are we building a system like datadog or metric monitoring for tech giant?\ninternal tool, non multi tenant \n\nq. features?\nDashboard : show metrics and aggregate them by time\nAlerts: in various channels like msg, on call alerts, slack etc\nMetrics:\nOS metrics: CPU, memory, disk usage\nhigh level concepts : RPS, server count, latency, throughput, availability\nbusiness metrics: custom can be defined\n\nq. scale?\n100 m DAU\nservices? 1000 services and 100 nodes for each and 100 metrics per service\n\nq. write frequency?\nrecord data every second\n\nq. do we need to compact the freq? like \n7 days, no compaction\n8 to 30 days, rol up to 1 min\n> 30 days < 1 year : roll up 10 mins\n> 1 year : archieve\n\nq. logs collection?\nno\n\nq. dist tracing?\nno\n\n\nFunctioanl req:\n1. View Dashboard : show metrics and aggregate them by time\n2. Send Alerts: in various channels like msg, on call alerts, slack etc\n3. Collect Metrics:\nOS metrics: CPU, memory, disk usage\nhigh level concepts : RPS, server count, latency, throughput, availability\nbusiness metrics: custom can be defined\n\nNFR:\n- Availability ( all 3 flows : 99.9)\n- Durability 11 9s\n- Scalable\n- Reliable and fault tolerant\n\nBack of teh enevelop calc:\nview dashboard:\n100 m DAU\n100 * 10^6 / 10^5 = 1000 rps\n\n1000 services * 100 nodes for each * 100 metrics per service\n= 10m metrics writes per second\n\nalerts:\nwhen alerts are raised, assume 0.1%\n10k alerts. pers sec\n\nservices? 1000 services and 100 nodes for each and 100 metrics per service",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
